Title: Local Physical Coodinates from Symplectic Projector Method

Authors: M.A. De Andrade, M.A. Santos and I.V. Vancea

Comments: 8 pages

Journal-ref: Mod.Phys.Lett. A16 (2001) 1907-1917

The basic arguments underlying the symplectic projector method are presented.By this method, local free coordinates on the constrait surface can be obtainedfor a broader class of constrained systems. Some interesting examples areanalyzed.